The paper is about modeling user relevance in information retrieval (IR), which is a core topic in the field of IR (cs.IR). The paper also mentions using feedback to capture the weights of different relevance dimensions, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a geometric model, which involves vector spaces, a common mathematical tool used in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses testing the hypothesis on data from a web search engine, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
